<FeaturePage
  title="Reactive Queries"
  description="Subscribe to a SurrealQL query once. sp00ky pushes fresh results the moment the underlying data changes."
  badge="Core · Library"
  activePath="/features"
>
  <p>
    sp00ky turns any SurrealQL query into a reactive subscription. Components declare what data
    they need — sp00ky takes care of keeping it fresh, invalidating the right rows, and pushing
    updates to every tab, window, and device that cares.
  </p>
  <p>
    No polling, no manual cache invalidation, no WebSocket boilerplate. Your view layer simply
    reads from a query result that’s always up to date.
  </p>
  <h2>Highlights</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Full SurrealQL — joins, graph traversals, live aggregates.</li>
    <li>Sub-50ms reactivity over a single multiplexed WebSocket.</li>
    <li>Automatic disposal when your component unmounts.</li>
    <li>Cross-tab invalidation built in.</li>
  </ul>
</FeaturePage>
